Fonts object > Attributes > FontsObject.allFonts

`app.fonts.allFonts`

Fonts object > Attributes > FontsObject.allFonts > Description

The list of all the fonts currently available on your system. They are grouped into what is named a family group which are Arrays of [Font object](#text-fontobject).

The Family Name of the group is simply the [familyName](#text-fontobject-fontobjectfamilyname) of any of the [Font objects](#text-fontobject) in the group. The Family Name in one font group is not guaranteed to have unique name compared to different font groups - the grouping is determined by a number of factors including the returned value of [FontObject.technology](#text-fontobject-fontobjecttechnology) and [FontObject.writingScripts](#text-fontobject-fontobjectwritingscripts). In addition, it is perfectly acceptable to have multiple fonts with the same PostScript name, though only one will have the same (PostScript name, Technology, Primary Writing Script) tuple. In the case of true duplicates, it is undefined which will be returned and which will be suppressed. The family groups and [Font objects](#text-fontobject) in the group are sorted according to the setting in the Character Panel dropdown "Show Font Names in English". If set to `true`, the [familyName](#text-fontobject-fontobjectfamilyname) and [styleName](#text-fontobject-fontobjectstylename) property is used, otherwise the [nativeFamilyName](#text-fontobject-fontobjectnativefamilyname) and [nativeStyleName](#text-fontobject-fontobjectnativestylename) property is used. [Font object](#text-fontobject) for which [isSubstitute](#text-fontobject-fontobjectissubstitute) returns `true` are always sorted to the end as individual family groups.

